Subject: Hodge Conjecture Problem Space

& [ProblemSpace] is formal mathematical framing
  + [domain] is algebraic geometry, complex geometry, topology, and Hodge theory
  + [core_objects] are nonsingular projective complex algebraic varieties, cohomology classes, Hodge classes, rational classes, and algebraic cycles
  + [central_question] is whether certain rational cohomology classes of type (p,p) are rational linear combinations of classes of algebraic cycles
  + [official_status] is open as of 2026-06-26 according to Clay Mathematics Institute public Millennium Problems framing
  + [authority_floor] is formal definitions, accepted theorem references, proof obligations, and peer-verifiable argument

& [Delineation] is the problem boundary
  + [inside] is the precise relation between Hodge classes and algebraic cycles on projective complex varieties
  + [boundary] is the gap between geometric/topological structure and algebraic representation
  + [outside] is metaphorical curvature-memory language unless translated into accepted algebraic geometry definitions

& [SupportNeeds] is required support for canonical work
  = need: exact statement variant and definitions
  = need: known partial results and counterexample boundaries for related generalized forms
  = need: claim inventory linking any proposed symbolic term to mathematical objects
